Hide stock status bar editor / keyboard-layout items (PRO-5559)

The RudderStack "IDE Footer" design (Figma node 101-3202) keeps only the
git branch, problems counts and notifications bell. Items added by
VS Code's built-in editor-status contribution and by the web keyboard
layout picker have no configuration toggle, so we short-circuit the
registration paths to drop them.

Each affected update* method has its body replaced with just a clear()
on the MutableDisposable so that nothing leaks into the status bar; the
surrounding state-tracking logic and command palette commands stay
intact. The bodies are fully replaced (not prepended with `return;`)
to avoid TS7027 under `allowUnreachableCode: false`. Users can still
re-enable the items by overriding the relevant settings (where they
exist) or by carrying their own fork.

